dc_description_s: U.S.G.S. 7.5 minute series (topographic) North Decimal Degree 41.375000. South Decimal Degree 41.250000. East Decimal Degree -74.625000. West Decimal Degree -74.750000. Alternate title: Port Jervis South, NJ--NY--PA. Polyconic projection. Universal transverse Mercator grids are shown. Relief shown by 20 feet contour interval and spot heights. Datum is mean sea level. "Mapped by the Army Map Service; published for civil use by the United States Geological Survey. Control by USC&GS. Topography by photogrammetric methods from aerial photographs taken 1942. Field checked 1943." Map is temporarily filed in the Reserve Course Materials Collection.
dc_title_s: Port Jervis South Quadrangle, New Jersey--New York--Pennsylvania. 7.5 minute series (topographic)
